{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"RED baseline test suite: inject the full LLM-failure matrix through the pydantic-ai `model_override` seam and pin rebar's CURRENT behavior, so later stories flip it to the new behavior with a regression net.\n\n## Why\nBefore changing behavior we must pin what rebar does today for every failure class and prove the offline injection harness works. The brainstorm validated on pydantic-ai 1.107.0 that a `FunctionModel` which raises `ModelHTTPError(429)` propagates with `status_code` intact, a canned `finish_reason` is readable at `result.response.finish_reason`, and `httpx.ReadTimeout` propagates unwrapped â€” so the harness is viable with no live/billable call.\n\n## What\nA parametrized RED test file injecting each failure class via a raising or canned pydantic-ai `FunctionModel` through the `PydanticAIRunner(model_override=...)` / `get_runner(override=...)` seams (`src/rebar/llm/runner.py:164,400`), asserting current behavior at two levels: (1) runner classification (everything collapses to `LLMUnavailableError` / `LLMRunnerError` today) and (2) gate end-to-end (plan-review systemic â†’ INDETERMINATE + claim blocked; completion â†’ fail-closed; code-review). Guarded by `pydantic_ai.models.ALLOW_MODEL_REQUESTS = False`.\n\n## Scope\n- Failure matrix: 429-rate, 429-insufficient_quota (body), 529, 500/503, `httpx.ConnectTimeout`, `httpx.ReadTimeout`, 401/403, 400 bad-request, 400 context-length, 413, `content_filter` finish_reason, `ContentFilterError`, length/truncation, `IncompleteToolCall`, unparseable output, validation-retry exhaustion, `UsageLimitExceeded` (request_limit=50), `tool_calls_limit`, unknown exception.\n- Two-scope scenarios: systemic (whole op) vs per-criterion (one unit among N).\n- Named liveness scenarios: a hung model request (a `FunctionModel` that sleeps past the per-request read timeout) is aborted+classified; a hung tool (a tool that sleeps past the per-tool timeout) is aborted+classified; a looping model (always returns a tool call) trips the step cap. These pin the `run_sync`-compatible zombie-run defense.\n- Guard tests: `--force` / `--force-close` / feature-disabled never enters the handling path.\n- Coverage boundary: `model_override` injects at the pydantic-ai MODEL layer, which is ABOVE the httpx transport where the retry lives â€” so transport-layer retry is NOT exercisable here; it is covered by the transport-injection spike in story 95a5. This suite covers classification + gate behavior + silent-success, not the transport.\n- NOT in scope: the NEW behavior (asserted GREEN by later stories) â€” this story pins CURRENT behavior only.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A parametrized test file (e.g. `tests/unit/test_llm_failure_matrix.py`) exercises every failure class via `model_override`, offline, guarded by `ALLOW_MODEL_REQUESTS=False`.\n- [ ] Each case asserts the current runner-level and gate-level behavior with a source citation comment.\n- [ ] Two-scope (systemic vs per-criterion) and force/disabled guard scenarios are covered.\n- [ ] `make test` passes; the file is the named baseline that later stories flip to the new behavior."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783560006118606001,"uuid":"8f7f2755-f993-42db-bf9e-01fc1e6948ba"}